WEBVTT

00:01.980 --> 00:05.460
[INTRO MUSIC]

00:10.420 --> 00:14.970
ANNOUNCER: And now, DreamWorks'
"The Penguins of Madagascar."

00:14.970 --> 00:18.920
[THEME MUSIC]

00:35.510 --> 00:36.210
-Hit it!

00:36.210 --> 00:39.360
[DANCE MUSIC]

00:49.650 --> 00:51.140
[CAMERA CLICK]

00:51.140 --> 00:52.370
-Cute and cuddly, boys.

00:56.110 --> 01:00.080
[INTRO MUSIC]

01:06.980 --> 01:08.860
RADIO: Yup, summer in NYC.

01:08.860 --> 01:10.490
The heat goes on.

01:10.490 --> 01:12.780
Temperatures expected to
hit record highs again

01:12.780 --> 01:15.590
today with no relief in sight.

01:15.590 --> 01:20.360
-Sky Spirits, I vow to continue
shaking my booty until you cry

01:20.360 --> 01:23.590
your cool tears of
rain down upon us.

01:23.590 --> 01:25.600
Mort, shake a little
more to the left.

01:25.600 --> 01:27.700
Maurice, keep your arms up!

01:27.700 --> 01:30.660
-Either I'm hallucinating,
or the bouncy is melting.

01:30.660 --> 01:32.460
-I am stroking.

01:32.460 --> 01:35.270
The heat.

01:35.270 --> 01:39.590
-We need some
fresh dancing legs.

01:39.590 --> 01:42.190
-Kowalski, how's that
deck temperature looking?

01:42.190 --> 01:44.360
-Let's see.

01:44.360 --> 01:51.100
I would describe the surface
as a searing inferno of agony.

01:51.100 --> 01:52.170
-Poetic.

01:52.170 --> 01:54.430
Private, what have we got
between us and the water?

01:54.430 --> 01:56.980
-I'm picking up some
small patches of shade

01:56.980 --> 01:59.560
at two, four, and six meters.

01:59.560 --> 02:00.260
-Right.

02:00.260 --> 02:01.420
Follow my lead.

02:01.420 --> 02:03.370
And-- go!

02:03.370 --> 02:06.620
[SHRIEKING]

02:06.620 --> 02:08.060
-And-- go!

02:08.060 --> 02:10.010
[SHRIEKING]

02:10.010 --> 02:11.190
-Oh.

02:11.190 --> 02:12.940
And-- go!

02:12.940 --> 02:13.640
Now!

02:13.640 --> 02:15.200
[SHRIEKING]

02:15.200 --> 02:16.630
-Hey, birds!

02:16.630 --> 02:21.770
I command you to join us in
our rain dancing at once!

02:21.770 --> 02:24.580
-Not much on rhythm, but
gotta love the enthusiasm.

02:24.580 --> 02:27.340
-I smell burning feet!

02:27.340 --> 02:30.970
-Every man for himself!

02:30.970 --> 02:33.670
-Uh-oh.

02:33.670 --> 02:34.590
-Our water!

02:34.590 --> 02:35.670
It's all gone.

02:35.670 --> 02:38.250
-They've drained
our entire pool!

02:38.250 --> 02:40.300
-Those maniacs!

02:40.300 --> 02:42.660
Do not ever get between
a penguin and his water.

02:42.660 --> 02:43.350
-Must swim.

02:43.350 --> 02:44.330
Must swim.

02:44.330 --> 02:45.070
Must swim.

02:45.070 --> 02:46.010
-Never!

02:46.010 --> 02:47.110
MARLENE: Uh, guys.

02:47.110 --> 02:49.160
It's not just you.

02:49.160 --> 02:52.470
They drained all the pools
across the entire zoo.

02:52.470 --> 02:53.770
[GASPING]

02:53.770 --> 02:56.860
SKIPPER: Gentlemen,
this is our destination.

02:56.860 --> 03:00.620
The cool, clear, and refreshing
water of the East River.

03:00.620 --> 03:03.870
-It's-- it's like a
storybook fairy tale.

03:03.870 --> 03:07.490
-But, Skipper, can we make
it with Alice watching?

03:07.490 --> 03:08.430
-Nope.

03:08.430 --> 03:09.690
Which is why she's leaving.

03:09.690 --> 03:11.650
RADIO: We're giving
away one all-expense

03:11.650 --> 03:14.890
paid cruise to our third caller.

03:14.890 --> 03:16.060
[DIAL TONE]

03:17.370 --> 03:18.680
[RINGING]

03:18.680 --> 03:20.350
RADIO: Congratulations.

03:20.350 --> 03:21.880
You're our third caller.

03:21.880 --> 03:24.600
That means you are the winner
of a free weekend cruise.

03:24.600 --> 03:25.300
-Huh?

03:25.300 --> 03:26.000
What's that?

03:26.000 --> 03:27.420
A free weekend cruise!

03:27.420 --> 03:28.620
Uh, yeah.

03:28.620 --> 03:29.320
OK.

03:29.320 --> 03:30.350
I can do that.

03:30.350 --> 03:32.960
SKIPPER: Bon voyage, Alice.

03:32.960 --> 03:36.440
Looks like she'll be off our
backs for the next three days.

03:36.440 --> 03:39.070
-And look, that must be her
substitute arriving now.

03:39.070 --> 03:39.770
-Whatstitute?

03:48.440 --> 03:49.380
-Officer X?

03:49.380 --> 03:52.140
-Now apparently
Zookeeper X. He's

03:52.140 --> 03:54.150
come back to exact his revenge.

03:54.150 --> 03:55.890
-Don't be ridiculous.

03:55.890 --> 03:59.370
He's probably forgotten
all about us by now.

03:59.370 --> 04:00.960
-Hmm-- penguins.

04:00.960 --> 04:02.250
-Uh-oh.

04:02.250 --> 04:04.020
-Is everyone in position?

04:04.020 --> 04:04.890
OK.

04:04.890 --> 04:09.270
Now, do the thunder puma stomp.

04:09.270 --> 04:12.260
And now do the
termal shower shake.

04:12.260 --> 04:12.960
Uh-huh.

04:12.960 --> 04:16.000
Oh, yes.

04:16.000 --> 04:16.690
Yes!

04:16.690 --> 04:17.680
Yes!

04:17.680 --> 04:19.360
It's working!

04:19.360 --> 04:24.720
Ah, the sweet taste
of raining water.

04:24.720 --> 04:26.570
-Actually, that's just my sweat.

04:26.570 --> 04:27.270
-OK.

04:27.270 --> 04:29.140
That would explain
the saltiness.

04:29.140 --> 04:30.860
-Well, well, well.

04:30.860 --> 04:32.100
It's the penguins.

04:32.100 --> 04:34.400
I say that the four
of you made just one

04:34.400 --> 04:36.240
tiny mistake the
last time we met.

04:36.240 --> 04:38.170
You didn't finish me off.

04:38.170 --> 04:39.410
-That's what I said.

04:39.410 --> 04:42.100
-This time, I'm
the one in charge.

04:42.100 --> 04:43.570
So if you're thinking
about making mischief,

04:43.570 --> 04:45.240
you better think again.

04:45.240 --> 04:47.690
Because you're all
in my house now.

04:47.690 --> 04:50.250
Oh, what's the matter?

04:50.250 --> 04:52.600
You boys sweating a
bit under the hot sun?

04:52.600 --> 04:55.810
-Technically, penguins
don't perspire so much as--

04:55.810 --> 04:56.800
-Get used to it!

04:56.800 --> 04:59.190
Because the sun is nothing
compared to the heat

04:59.190 --> 05:01.340
I'm bringing out of
your feathered butts.

05:01.340 --> 05:03.170
I am the Sahara in July.

05:03.170 --> 05:06.530
I'm a five-alarm fury
burning out of control.

05:06.530 --> 05:09.120
I am molten magma mayhem.

05:11.690 --> 05:13.200
-Hey, Skipper?

05:13.200 --> 05:14.200
What about pudding?

05:14.200 --> 05:15.720
What about the East River?

05:15.720 --> 05:17.940
-Zookeeper X is going
to be all over ups

05:17.940 --> 05:19.810
every second of every day.

05:19.810 --> 05:21.460
-Then we go at night.

05:25.070 --> 05:28.430
-If we make it to Lex, we can
catch the E train to the river.

05:28.430 --> 05:29.850
-Rico, token us.

05:34.550 --> 05:36.200
OFFICER X: Sorry, penguins.

05:36.200 --> 05:38.880
But you birds are all
catching the Officer

05:38.880 --> 05:42.230
X-press to nowheres.

05:42.230 --> 05:42.930
-Run!

05:53.360 --> 05:54.580
-Skipper, what now?

05:54.580 --> 05:55.430
RICO: Must swim!

05:55.430 --> 05:56.130
Must swim!

05:59.210 --> 06:00.120
-We dig.

06:04.140 --> 06:06.450
-I just need to
calculate precisely

06:06.450 --> 06:08.800
where we should break through.

06:08.800 --> 06:11.300
Huh?

06:11.300 --> 06:13.540
OFFICER X: X marks the spot.

06:13.540 --> 06:15.230
[LAUGHING]

06:15.710 --> 06:16.410
RICO: Must swim!

06:16.410 --> 06:17.110
Must swim!

06:20.710 --> 06:24.560
-Not even Alice knows about
this backup ventilation shaft.

06:24.560 --> 06:26.450
OFFICER X: Allow me
to blow your mind.

06:32.710 --> 06:33.920
-X!

06:33.920 --> 06:36.630
X!

06:36.630 --> 06:38.520
X!

06:38.520 --> 06:40.900
X again!

06:40.900 --> 06:42.880
-I don't understand it.

06:42.880 --> 06:45.310
-It's like he's always
one step ahead of us.

06:45.310 --> 06:46.010
-Yup.

06:46.010 --> 06:49.760
-It seems I've turned
your world upside down.

06:49.760 --> 06:50.460
Hmm?

06:56.240 --> 06:58.730
-Men, I've lost battles before.

06:58.730 --> 07:00.040
That I can handle.

07:00.040 --> 07:02.810
But he keeps zinging us
with those one-liners.

07:02.810 --> 07:04.040
I won't have it!

07:04.040 --> 07:05.600
-Skipper, what are
we going to do?

07:05.600 --> 07:07.050
-Something very rash.

07:07.050 --> 07:08.030
Something totally unexpected.

07:35.240 --> 07:40.200
-According to this compass, the
East River is due-- thataway!

07:40.200 --> 07:41.060
[MUMBLING]

07:41.060 --> 07:42.000
-Roger that.

07:42.000 --> 07:43.450
Any sign of X?

07:43.450 --> 07:44.730
-It's all clear, Skipper.

07:44.730 --> 07:47.340
-And at 400 feet and
climbing, I don't

07:47.340 --> 07:49.340
think there's much chance
at running into him.

07:49.340 --> 07:51.420
We're home free.

07:51.420 --> 07:53.240
-I guess you're right, Skipper.

07:53.240 --> 07:55.430
You know, unless
Officer X did something

07:55.430 --> 07:58.880
like hide inside the pretzel
cart before we took off.

07:58.880 --> 08:01.080
Well, you have to admit
it's kind of strange.

08:01.080 --> 08:02.710
We ran all over
the zoo gathering

08:02.710 --> 08:07.560
supplies and didn't see
Officer X. Not even once.

08:07.560 --> 08:10.820
I'm just saying it's possible
that Officer X could have

08:10.820 --> 08:13.980
anticipated our plan and might
have hidden in the cart's

08:13.980 --> 08:17.440
pretzel department
before we took off.

08:17.440 --> 08:20.780
[LAUGHING]

08:21.730 --> 08:26.040
-Why that has to be just
the most ridiculous--

08:26.040 --> 08:30.140
-You can't possibly imagine the
statistical improbability that,

08:30.140 --> 08:30.840
well--

08:30.840 --> 08:37.580
-That Officer X-- the Officer
X is hiding down there.

08:37.580 --> 08:41.140
-Just inches below
our very feet.

08:41.140 --> 08:43.200
-Well, the very idea.

08:43.200 --> 08:45.400
I mean it's-- it's
just that it's so--

08:45.400 --> 08:48.450
-It's so-- so-- so--

08:48.450 --> 08:49.560
-So totally obvious!

08:49.560 --> 08:50.260
Battlestations!

08:53.690 --> 08:55.450
On three.

08:55.450 --> 08:59.950
One, two-- I can't do it.

08:59.950 --> 09:01.670
I mean what if he's
really in there.

09:01.670 --> 09:04.010
What if we at least start with
one of those witty one-liners.

09:04.010 --> 09:05.190
Probably something
about pretzels.

09:05.190 --> 09:10.480
-Something like I'll bet you
never expected this twist.

09:10.480 --> 09:11.390
-Exactly.

09:11.390 --> 09:14.200
-Come on, now you're
the ones being silly.

09:14.200 --> 09:14.900
Look.

09:14.900 --> 09:16.400
See for yourselves.

09:16.400 --> 09:17.690
-Yeah, he's right.

09:17.690 --> 09:19.410
There's nothing there.

09:19.410 --> 09:21.110
-Nothing but pretzel salt.

09:21.110 --> 09:22.110
OFFICER X: Evening, boys.

09:22.110 --> 09:25.800
This is where I rub some
salt into the wound.

09:34.900 --> 09:37.790
-Mort, shift three
inches to your left.

09:37.790 --> 09:40.060
Maurice, grab Mort's tail.

09:40.060 --> 09:42.000
Well, Sky Spirits?

09:42.000 --> 09:45.280
Are we getting warmer here?

09:45.280 --> 09:46.160
Give us a sign.

09:49.920 --> 09:51.940
-Well, it's raining penguins.

09:51.940 --> 09:53.430
I guess that's a sign.

09:59.200 --> 10:00.430
-Skipper!

10:00.430 --> 10:01.130
Help!

10:04.490 --> 10:07.900
-Mort, did you just
have the audacity

10:07.900 --> 10:11.490
to kick your stinking foot
into the sacred temple

10:11.490 --> 10:12.970
of my royal buttocks?

10:16.930 --> 10:18.270
Well, keep doing it!

10:18.270 --> 10:18.970
Go, go!

10:28.120 --> 10:28.980
Yes.

10:28.980 --> 10:29.840
Kick me, Mort.

10:29.840 --> 10:30.920
Harder!

10:30.920 --> 10:32.230
To the left one.

10:32.230 --> 10:33.290
Another right one.

10:33.290 --> 10:34.090
Keep them coming.

10:34.090 --> 10:35.600
It's working!

10:35.600 --> 10:36.440
Yes!

10:36.440 --> 10:37.140
Ouch.

10:37.140 --> 10:37.880
Yes!

10:37.880 --> 10:38.260
Ow.

10:38.260 --> 10:38.990
Wait.

10:38.990 --> 10:40.730
That last one kind
of hurt a little bit.

10:43.660 --> 10:44.710
-Of course.

10:44.710 --> 10:45.950
It's the salt.

10:45.950 --> 10:48.780
The sodium granules released
from the pretzel cart

10:48.780 --> 10:50.480
into the convective
cloud layer must

10:50.480 --> 10:53.750
have sparked a freezing
nucleation reaction.

10:53.750 --> 10:54.880
And boom!

10:54.880 --> 10:58.170
Instant rain.

10:58.170 --> 11:00.380
-Sky Spirits-- thank you.

11:00.380 --> 11:01.530
Ow.

11:01.530 --> 11:04.480
Thank you for this
wonderful-- ow.

11:04.480 --> 11:07.800
Mort, you can stop
kicking me now.

11:07.800 --> 11:09.150
Mort.

11:09.150 --> 11:10.340
Mort!

11:10.340 --> 11:11.620
Hello.

11:11.620 --> 11:14.430
Maurice, will you get
this maniac off my booty!

11:20.030 --> 11:22.540
-Well, well, well.

11:22.540 --> 11:25.190
Looks like I'm finally
going to get my payback.

11:25.190 --> 11:27.740
SKIPPER: Sorry,
Loser X, but no sail.

11:30.390 --> 11:31.090
Ha!

11:31.090 --> 11:32.010
Zinger.

11:32.010 --> 11:32.710
Gotcha.

11:37.790 --> 11:39.460
-Home again, home again.

11:42.300 --> 11:45.150
[SCREAMING]

11:46.090 --> 11:47.040
-Well, Skipper.

11:47.040 --> 11:48.630
I'd say mission accomplished.

11:48.630 --> 11:49.330
-Yup.

11:49.330 --> 11:51.940
And did you catch
my no sail line.

11:51.940 --> 11:53.650
You know, with
the cash register?

11:53.650 --> 11:57.520
Not a bad way to end.

11:57.520 --> 12:01.490
[INTRO MUSIC]

12:09.960 --> 12:11.650
KOWALSKI: Positive
ID on deli owner.

12:11.650 --> 12:13.300
Approaching the refrigerator.

12:13.300 --> 12:14.000
-And?

12:14.000 --> 12:14.480
-And?

12:14.480 --> 12:15.350
-It's?

12:15.350 --> 12:17.630
KOWALSKI: We have
day old tuna salad.

12:17.630 --> 12:18.980
[CHEERING]

12:18.980 --> 12:20.210
-He's off to the store room.

12:20.210 --> 12:22.100
Definitely a dump job.

12:22.100 --> 12:25.030
-I can't believe people
just throw away old tuna.

12:25.030 --> 12:26.690
I mean what is
salmonella anyway?

12:26.690 --> 12:29.010
-I believe it's Italian
for little salmon.

12:29.010 --> 12:32.070
-Ah, a taste of the old country.

12:32.070 --> 12:34.890
[SPEAKING ITALIAN]

12:34.890 --> 12:37.260
-Kowalski, tuna
extraction options?

12:37.260 --> 12:40.200
-That skylight is
our entry point.

12:40.200 --> 12:42.050
I suggest the parasail.

12:42.050 --> 12:45.360
Quick and silent.

12:45.360 --> 12:48.250
[ZAPPING]

12:48.250 --> 12:50.470
-With a slight chance of
dancing the high voltage chacha.

12:55.170 --> 12:55.990
-What?

12:55.990 --> 12:57.480
Maybe that's just
how I fly, all right?

13:00.530 --> 13:02.480
-Is that really the
safest approach?

13:02.480 --> 13:03.830
-Psh, no.

13:03.830 --> 13:06.320
But using wind and
velocity calculations,

13:06.320 --> 13:11.430
I've determined the ideal body
shape for clear parasailing.

13:11.430 --> 13:12.890
[NERVOUS SIGH]

13:12.890 --> 13:15.340
[YELLING]

13:17.300 --> 13:18.460
SKIPPER: Release Private!

13:18.460 --> 13:22.900
Fly, you magnificent beast!

13:22.900 --> 13:24.670
[SQUEALING]

13:24.670 --> 13:25.370
-Whoa!

13:25.370 --> 13:26.350
Whoa!

13:26.350 --> 13:27.340
Whoa!

13:27.340 --> 13:28.330
Ha ha!

13:28.330 --> 13:29.230
I made it.

13:29.230 --> 13:29.930
-He's clear.

13:29.930 --> 13:30.780
[CHEERING]

13:30.780 --> 13:32.380
-Approaching skylight.

13:32.380 --> 13:35.110
This is the greatest
thrill of my life.

13:35.110 --> 13:37.930
Ah!

13:37.930 --> 13:38.840
-He missed it.

13:38.840 --> 13:40.230
-No tuna!

13:40.230 --> 13:42.620
I mean, Private's in danger?

13:42.620 --> 13:44.910
-No, he's descending
safely next door.

13:44.910 --> 13:46.780
Kowalski, what's on
the left of the deli?

13:46.780 --> 13:49.910
-I believe that would be
Madam Hilda's Training

13:49.910 --> 13:51.670
School for Bad-tempered
Rottweilers.

13:51.670 --> 13:52.590
-Uh-oh.

13:52.590 --> 13:56.020
[BARKING, SCREAMING]

13:56.720 --> 13:58.970
[KNOCKING]

14:01.800 --> 14:02.750
-Oh, my.

14:02.750 --> 14:04.630
How did you get down there?

14:04.630 --> 14:05.440
Never mind.

14:05.440 --> 14:06.230
Come, come.

14:06.230 --> 14:08.530
Let's have a look.

14:08.530 --> 14:09.230
-Ow!

14:09.230 --> 14:10.700
Ow!

14:10.700 --> 14:11.670
Ow!

14:11.670 --> 14:13.400
-Just bumps and bruises.

14:13.400 --> 14:14.600
Don't worry, little one.

14:14.600 --> 14:17.030
My new intern will
take good care of you.

14:17.030 --> 14:19.090
Shawna, your first
patient is ready.

14:23.440 --> 14:24.470
-Look at you, soldier.

14:24.470 --> 14:27.570
Freshly decorated
with combat souvenirs.

14:27.570 --> 14:30.030
Who cares if we didn't
get the tuna salad?

14:30.030 --> 14:31.450
-Uh, me?

14:31.450 --> 14:34.790
-Now you own your
pain like a real man.

14:34.790 --> 14:35.490
Sorry.

14:35.490 --> 14:37.160
Seriously, couldn't be prouder.

14:40.070 --> 14:40.770
-Funny.

14:40.770 --> 14:42.410
I don't feel very manly.

14:42.410 --> 14:44.220
-Knock, knock.

14:44.220 --> 14:45.110
Oh, my gosh!

14:45.110 --> 14:46.600
Aren't you just the
cutest thing ever?

15:02.100 --> 15:02.920
Cootchie-coo!

15:02.920 --> 15:04.610
Oh, does that tickle.

15:07.880 --> 15:09.710
You are so sweet.

15:13.570 --> 15:17.080
-Oh, I wish this
morning would never end.

15:17.080 --> 15:17.780
-OK.

15:17.780 --> 15:18.600
Back to the habitat.

15:18.600 --> 15:19.300
-No!

15:19.300 --> 15:20.000
Shawna!

15:23.060 --> 15:23.760
-Hey!

15:23.760 --> 15:25.240
What is it?

15:25.240 --> 15:26.230
Let go of it!

15:29.200 --> 15:31.900
This isn't a game, spa princess.

15:31.900 --> 15:34.470
No more owies, no more hospital.

15:34.470 --> 15:36.800
-Owies.

15:36.800 --> 15:39.130
-Surprise!

15:39.130 --> 15:40.520
-You really didn't
have to do this.

15:40.520 --> 15:42.110
[SHUSHING]

15:42.110 --> 15:44.540
-Anything our
wounded hero wants.

15:44.540 --> 15:46.250
Today's your special day.

15:46.250 --> 15:46.950
-(SINGING) Fishcake!

15:49.920 --> 15:52.200
-Well actually,
what I'd really like

15:52.200 --> 15:54.930
is another crack at
parachuting into the deli.

15:54.930 --> 15:56.320
You know, get back on the horse.

15:56.320 --> 15:58.720
Laugh in the face
of danger and such.

15:58.720 --> 16:00.350
[WHIMPERING]

16:00.350 --> 16:01.240
-Skipper?

16:01.240 --> 16:04.780
-Remember when I said I
couldn't be any prouder?

16:04.780 --> 16:05.940
I was wrong.

16:05.940 --> 16:07.160
I was wrong!

16:10.580 --> 16:11.930
-Release velocity achieved.

16:11.930 --> 16:12.630
Go!

16:18.370 --> 16:21.530
Skylight entrance in
five, four, three--

16:21.530 --> 16:22.480
-Oh, Shawna.

16:26.280 --> 16:29.190
SKIPPER: Uh, Kowalski, what's
on the right side of the deli?

16:29.190 --> 16:31.580
I believe that
would be Gunnerson's

16:31.580 --> 16:33.100
House of Rusty Bear Traps.

16:33.100 --> 16:34.520
-Oh, boy.

16:34.520 --> 16:37.370
[SCREAMING, CLAMPING]

16:37.370 --> 16:39.400
SHAWNA: Aw, back already?

16:39.400 --> 16:40.320
Poor guy.

16:40.320 --> 16:42.380
You must be the unluckiest
animal in the zoo.

16:44.730 --> 16:45.430
-Funny.

16:45.430 --> 16:48.190
I feel like the
luckiest penguin alive.

16:48.190 --> 16:49.110
-All better.

16:49.110 --> 16:51.790
Now let's hope I don't
see you in here again.

16:51.790 --> 16:53.710
-No power on Earth
could keep me away.

16:56.240 --> 16:58.100
PENGUINS: Surprise!

16:58.100 --> 16:58.800
-What?

16:58.800 --> 17:01.120
You made me another cake.

17:01.120 --> 17:01.960
-Nope.

17:01.960 --> 17:03.650
-Oh, um, no thanks.

17:03.650 --> 17:07.880
You've earned some serious
relaxation time, soldier.

17:07.880 --> 17:10.160
-I've got magazines.

17:10.160 --> 17:13.630
Oh, oh, this one has
unicorns and quilting.

17:13.630 --> 17:16.800
-Oh, any quilts with unicorns?

17:16.800 --> 17:17.610
[GAWKING]

17:18.800 --> 17:19.770
-No, no!

17:19.770 --> 17:23.400
I insist on another tuna
salad recovery mission.

17:23.400 --> 17:26.510
I shall conquer or get
moderately into trying.

17:26.510 --> 17:28.170
-Private, are you sure you--

17:28.170 --> 17:31.110
-Don't feed the boy
your doubter's poison.

17:31.110 --> 17:35.140
He has got to pummelled this
bad luck streak into submission.

17:35.140 --> 17:37.050
Anytime you're ready.

17:37.050 --> 17:38.140
Private?

17:38.140 --> 17:38.840
-Now's good.

17:57.330 --> 17:58.820
[WHISTLE BLOWING]

18:00.310 --> 18:02.800
-Whoa!

18:02.800 --> 18:04.760
[BUZZING]

18:07.230 --> 18:08.720
[GAWKING]

18:11.640 --> 18:15.270
[GROANING]

18:16.190 --> 18:18.730
-Frankly, boys, I;m starting
to think Private's bad

18:18.730 --> 18:21.100
luck streak may be unprominable.

18:21.100 --> 18:21.940
-Egad!

18:21.940 --> 18:22.840
-I know!

18:22.840 --> 18:24.190
Tough word, right?

18:24.190 --> 18:25.490
Unpomelable.

18:25.490 --> 18:26.190
Try it.

18:26.190 --> 18:27.690
-No, I mean egad!

18:27.690 --> 18:28.810
Look at this.

18:28.810 --> 18:31.290
Private's harness was
cut before that last run.

18:31.290 --> 18:33.180
This is no bad luck streak.

18:33.180 --> 18:34.540
It's sabotage.

18:34.540 --> 18:35.660
-Sabotage?

18:35.660 --> 18:36.550
-Impossible.

18:36.550 --> 18:38.920
No one else had access
to that parasail.

18:38.920 --> 18:40.610
The saboteur would
have to be one of us.

18:40.610 --> 18:41.310
-1-2-3 not it!

18:41.310 --> 18:42.090
-Not it!

18:42.090 --> 18:42.790
-What?

18:42.790 --> 18:44.310
-Ah, he admits his guilt.

18:47.250 --> 18:49.630
[MUMBLING]

18:50.330 --> 18:51.570
-Oh, no I didn't.

18:51.570 --> 18:52.350
You started it.

18:52.350 --> 18:53.070
-Hey, Private.

18:53.070 --> 18:55.750
Did you know Rico was
secretly sabotaging-- what

18:55.750 --> 18:58.630
in the name of corn-fed
candy stripers?

18:58.630 --> 19:01.310
-Seriously, is this like
the eighth time today?

19:01.310 --> 19:03.450
-I'm going to call you
Mr. Butterflippers.

19:03.450 --> 19:06.110
-I guess I just must
be accident prone.

19:06.110 --> 19:06.810
[GASPING]

19:06.810 --> 19:08.160
-Air quotes.

19:08.160 --> 19:10.860
The mime of insincerity.

19:10.860 --> 19:12.380
He's lying.

19:12.380 --> 19:13.900
-Sorry, compadre.

19:13.900 --> 19:16.260
Looks like this
was an inside job.

19:16.260 --> 19:19.870
Inside Private's own
puppy love-twisted brain.

19:19.870 --> 19:22.290
-Be right back.

19:22.290 --> 19:23.050
-Be right here.

19:23.050 --> 19:23.750
Sighing longingly.

19:26.770 --> 19:27.470
Ah!

19:27.470 --> 19:29.380
-Accident prone, Private?

19:29.380 --> 19:31.930
Oh, I've seen accident prone.

19:31.930 --> 19:34.970
Try Manfredi and Johnson,
with a Chinese lantern.

19:34.970 --> 19:37.070
And six bottles of rocket fuel!

19:37.070 --> 19:38.870
-Worst talent show ever.

19:38.870 --> 19:40.120
-All right, I admit it.

19:40.120 --> 19:41.950
I did it all to be was Shawna.

19:41.950 --> 19:43.560
But you don't understand.

19:43.560 --> 19:46.090
When Shawna bandages you,
you're like an angel cake

19:46.090 --> 19:47.430
being frosting by fairies.

19:47.430 --> 19:48.890
-Uh, what?

19:48.890 --> 19:50.320
-You know nothing about love.

19:50.320 --> 19:52.540
-Oh, relax, young Private.

19:52.540 --> 19:54.320
Actually we do understand.

19:54.320 --> 19:55.720
-You-- you do?

19:55.720 --> 19:56.420
-Of course.

19:56.420 --> 19:58.480
Who hasn't gone
stupid for a lady?

19:58.480 --> 19:59.990
-Me.

19:59.990 --> 20:01.580
-Guatemala?

20:01.580 --> 20:03.590
Doris the Dolphin?

20:03.590 --> 20:07.200
Don't make me show
everyone the tattoo.

20:07.200 --> 20:08.200
-(SOBBING) Doris.

20:08.200 --> 20:11.320
-But the important thing
is to take a deep breath.

20:11.320 --> 20:16.150
Realise you've gone too
far, and snap out of it!

20:16.150 --> 20:18.860
-Yes, that does
make a lot of sense.

20:18.860 --> 20:19.560
No!

20:19.560 --> 20:20.550
I'll never leave!

20:20.550 --> 20:22.540
Shawna is my destiny.

20:22.540 --> 20:23.490
[EXCLAIMS]

20:26.470 --> 20:28.420
-Is this why my sweet little
guy's been in the hospital

20:28.420 --> 20:29.120
so much?

20:29.120 --> 20:31.740
Are the other
penguins bullying you?

20:31.740 --> 20:34.920
Don't you dare.

20:34.920 --> 20:35.840
-Oh!

20:35.840 --> 20:37.500
[WHIMPERING]

20:38.200 --> 20:39.240
-Easy.

20:39.240 --> 20:41.020
I'm not going to hurt you.

20:41.020 --> 20:45.940
-Sister, I'd like
to see you-- OK,

20:45.940 --> 20:49.800
the lady is not
without her charm.

20:49.800 --> 20:50.840
-Of course.

20:50.840 --> 20:52.830
Avian insanity fever.

20:52.830 --> 20:54.580
-Avian insanity?

20:54.580 --> 20:57.210
Where'd she get that
crackpot diagnosis?

20:57.210 --> 21:00.200
[GROWLING]

21:01.100 --> 21:02.240
-No problem.

21:02.240 --> 21:05.300
A simple injection
should mellow them out.

21:05.300 --> 21:06.010
-Needle!

21:06.010 --> 21:10.330
[MUMBLING]

21:15.130 --> 21:17.950
-You call this mellow--

21:17.950 --> 21:22.120
-(SLOWLY) Mama, I'm a
pretty, pretty butterfly!

21:22.120 --> 21:23.970
-Yeah.

21:23.970 --> 21:26.180
-Aw, don't worry, sweetie.

21:26.180 --> 21:28.280
You just say goodbye
to those bullies.

21:28.280 --> 21:32.220
You will never share a
habitat with them again.

21:32.220 --> 21:34.870
-Goodbye-- forever?

21:34.870 --> 21:36.770
But-- but that's not
what-- I didn't mean for--

21:36.770 --> 21:37.970
-It's OK, Private.

21:37.970 --> 21:42.690
All we want is for
you to be happy.

21:42.690 --> 21:45.490
-The thing is, Skipper, without
you three I don't think I

21:45.490 --> 21:47.960
could be.

21:47.960 --> 21:49.970
Forgive me, Shawna, for
that which I must do.

21:49.970 --> 21:50.670
-Whew.

21:50.670 --> 21:52.950
So we'll start quarantine
procedures, and--

21:52.950 --> 21:53.750
[MUMBLING]

21:53.750 --> 21:54.560
-Ah!

21:54.560 --> 21:57.190
OK, I'm just going to
pout this mask back on

21:57.190 --> 22:00.570
and take a teensy
little check of-- huh?

22:00.570 --> 22:01.570
-Baba-hooey!

22:01.570 --> 22:02.570
[SHRIEKING]

22:05.570 --> 22:06.880
-You've got it, too?

22:06.880 --> 22:08.890
And I've been
touching you all day?

22:08.890 --> 22:11.480
-Avian insanity!

22:11.480 --> 22:13.440
-Only contagious through saliva.

22:13.440 --> 22:15.480
Well, I didn't get
any of his spit on me.

22:15.480 --> 22:16.180
-Hello.

22:20.390 --> 22:23.390
-Ew!

22:23.390 --> 22:24.380
[DOOR CLOSES]

22:25.880 --> 22:26.780
-I'm sorry, Skipper.

22:26.780 --> 22:29.980
-That was a noble sacrifice
you made, Private.

22:29.980 --> 22:32.790
Maybe it's just the
medicine talking.

22:32.790 --> 22:34.340
Are you naked?

22:34.340 --> 22:36.170
Oh, we're all naked!

22:36.170 --> 22:38.340
-Um, no.

22:38.340 --> 22:39.780
-OK, it is medicine.

22:39.780 --> 22:42.340
Anyway, forget
what I said before.

22:42.340 --> 22:45.190
This is the proudest
I've ever been.

22:45.190 --> 22:47.180
-She really was wonderful.

22:47.180 --> 22:51.130
-And that's why you never beat
yourself up over the lady.

22:51.130 --> 22:53.620
Love has enough
sting of its own.

22:53.620 --> 22:54.490
-Almost forgot.

22:54.490 --> 22:56.340
PRIVATE: Ow!

22:56.340 --> 22:58.850
-Told ya.

22:58.850 --> 23:02.800
[THEME MUSIC]
